# A meterological phenomenon also known as a [[lunar rainbow]] or [[white rainbow]], well documented at Cumberland Falls near Corbin, Kentucky,  Victoria Falls in Africa as well as other places such as Yosemite National Park.
#:'' Known as the "Niagara of the South," the 125-foot wide curtain of water is dramatic day or night. But it's only at night during a full moon that you can see the '''moonbow''''' — [http://parks.ky.gov/resortparks/cf/ Cumberland Falls Resort (Kentucky) State Park.]

